Insurance
Add Attributes to a Child Spec

Most child specs include at least one attribute. When you add attributes to a child spec, you also configure them with controls and values.

On the Attributes tab, click New.
Choose the attribute category your attribute is in.
Choose the attribute.

(Optional) Edit the Attribute Name. This description isn't picked up by the services, added to any JSONs, or shown to users.
(Optional) Change the Name if you want it to display differently in the UI for this child spec.

Configure the attribute.

FIELD

	Is Hidden
		Select this option to hide this attribute from users.
	Is Configurable
		Leave this cleared to define this attribute with a blank value or a preset value that users can't change. 
			Suppose Add a Fixed Value to an Attribute on a Child Spec.
		Select this option to give users the flexibility to enter or select a value for this attribute. See Add a Configurable Value to an Attribute on a Child Spec.

	Rating
		Select this option to have Vlocity use this attribute's value to rate the product this child spec is attached to.

	Tax and Fee Rating Attribute
		Select this option to use this attribute's value to rate a tax or fee for either this child spec or for the root product this child spec is attached to.

	Required
		Select this option to make the attribute required for the claim involved injury and claim damaged property specs.

Add a Fixed Value to an Attribute on a Child Spec
A fixed attribute value is a blank value or a preset value that users can't change.
Add a Configurable Value to an Attribute on a Child Spec
A configurable attribute value gives users the flexibility to enter or select a value.
title: Adding Attributes to Insurance Child Specs
